{
  "schema_version": 1,
  "manifest_id": "quantified-alternation-boundary",
  "spec_refs": [
    "docs/benchmarks/plan.md",
    "docs/spec/drop-in-re-compatibility.md"
  ],
  "notes": [
    "Quantified-alternation boundary workloads keep captures, one literal alternation site repeated across a bounded `{1,2}` envelope, and tiny haystacks so the scorecard measures helper-call overhead for the newly supported quantified-alternation slice rather than regex throughput.",
    "Measured rows cover the bounded `a(b|c){1,2}d`, `a(?P<word>b|c){1,2}d`, `a((b|c)|de){1,2}d`, `a(?P<word>(b|c)|de){1,2}d`, `a((b|c)\\2){1,2}d`, `a(?P<outer>(?P<inner>b|c)(?P=inner)){1,2}d`, `a((b|c){1,2})?(?(1)d|e)`, and `a(?P<outer>(b|c){1,2})?(?(outer)d|e)` compile/search/fullmatch paths directly at representative absent, lower-bound, mixed-branch, and second-repetition haystacks, so bounded nested branches, conditionals, and branch-local backreferences inside quantified alternation now reach the published benchmark surface while wider counted ranges, open-ended repeats, and broader backtracking-heavy shapes stay as explicit known-gap rows until queued follow-ons land."
  ],
  "defaults": {
    "warmup_iterations": 2,
    "sample_iterations": 5,
    "timed_samples": 7
  },
  "workloads": [
